result.execSummary:
The defendant Dominique L Taylor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dominique L Taylor is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dominique L Taylor was found guilty of Possession of THC [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Dominique L Taylor was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Contrary to Court Order, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(d).
  • Dominique L Taylor was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Contrary to Court Order, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(d).
  • Dominique L Taylor was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Contrary to Court Order, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(d).
  • Dominique L Taylor was found guilty of Possess Firearm-Contrary to Court Order, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(d).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. - AODA assessment and treatment
